snippet.textDisplay: Hey Shane, I was wondering if you could do a series on DID and specifically talk with DissociaDID and TeamPinata  about the stigmas surrounding that specific disorder and why it's so misunderstood and that these people are not crazy or a threat to others. I think it would be good for someone with such a huge fan base to cover this topic and show people that DID is an actual thing and that the people who have it are not monsters or evil or scary. Each one of their Alters/Multiples/Personalities/Systems are real people with real emotions that deserve to be treated fairly and with respect and love and they deserve to be acknowledged. I doubt you'll see this but if you do please think about it. Thank you! And I love you so much! Your amazing! ❤️🥰 -From a Loyal Fan

snippet.textDisplay:
Our lives can be humming along fine until one carefully aimed comment slips through our sensitive firewall and BAM! Face-planted on that familiar cold cement block. Again. Back to square-one, dammit, until the day we die, or so it seems. Until the hurt turns into anger, the wound can’t start to close so I’m glad to watch you expressing real rage, physically and verbally. (Bet you can tell I’ve been there a few million times. I’ll be there a few more million times before I fly away from myself.)
One comment. Advanced pardons if you don’t like it & you probably won’t. You’ll never see this anyway so what the hell.
I’m so happy you’re surrounded by loved ones & caring souls. That’s your wealth right there, not what’s in the bank but you know that. Sooooo, you’re bummed majorly with good reason, yet friends love you, Ryland loves you, your animals love you, your fans love you (in their way), and still . . . I’m not seeing your eyes truly light up until the pretty presents containing bling are handed to you and that’s what made me use a little critical thinking and analysis. Material stuff & $$$ can distract for a while and contribute to a more comfortable life but they don’t MAKE any of us HAPPY unless we’re talking Jeffree Star & even with him, they don’t shield him from all suffering. So your depression lifted as your anger kicked in (good!), but as the gifts kept coming, it really got kicked to the curb. Those gifts are PRETTY, SPARKLY, GORGEOUS, HAND-MADE WITH LOVE BLINGY, ONE-OF-A-KIND DELIGHTS all for YOU & all of that is really, really good but . . . they’re external to you. They don’t crawl inside your psyche to provide a sturdy foundation of your well-being. The smiles they provide fade & eventually, they can’t diminish the depression any better than anything ever did before. Wish it were as easy for most people as it seems to be for Jeffree. (Even I know that act is at least a little bit crap.) Anyway, you’ll never see this. If ya do, you won’t care. You’re Shane Yaw/Dawson so you won’t ever have to. I gave it a shot, anyway. Just don’t pin your happiness or security or popularity or self image or acceptance or worth or future on anything external to yourself and your precious loved ones.
